metrics_conclusion: In terms of chords and melody, Bohemian Rhapsody is more complex than the typical song, having above average scores in Chord Complexity, Melodic Complexity, Chord Progression Novelty and Chord-Bass Melody.
key_conclusion: Bohemian Rhapsody has sections analyzed in the following keys: B♭ Major, E♭ Major,  and A Major.  Click on the linked cheat sheets for popular chords, chord progressions, downloadable midi files and more!

metadata.editComments: fixed the melody. it wasn't following any of the harmony parts being sung.
Labeling the Abmaj7 as IVmaj7/IV doesn't make any sense since it's followed by ii. This is simply modal interchange from Mixolydian - nothing functional going on here.
fixed rhythm added a 7 to a chord
Made the melody a bit more truthful to the original and took a 7 from a chord that doesn’t have one
fixed the vid sync. Added the two missing bars. fixed the guitar riff melody.

Analyzing the chord in bar 4 as vii°7/iii doesn't make much sense considering the fact that it's followed by a V chord. Due to the symmetrical nature of fully diminished seventh chords, every chord tone can be regarded as the root, so thinking of this chord as vii°/V makes much more sense.
